gomodel:SYNGO_406  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1: colocalization of BACE1 with synaptophysin at the light microscopic level.\nFig. 3: localization of BACE1 at the presynaptic within mossy fiber terminals terminal at the electron microscopic level.\nFig. 4: colocalization of BACE1 with synaptophysin around amyloid plaques\nin 5XFAD transgenic mouse and human AD brains.\n\nNote: BACE1 is localized at mossy fiber terminals. Therefore glutamatergic annotation is made.\n\n13/4/2017 Pim\n-Literal: \"In addition, our data suggest that BACE1 is present in vesicles, some in close proximity to synaptic active zones, although the exact identity of BACE1-containing vesicles has yet to be determined.\". Experimental description: Experiments in brain slices are from mouse. Fig. 4 shows also a staining of human brain from AD patients.\n\nLiteral M&M\n\n\"Animals\n5XFAD mice have been described previously [75] and were\nmaintained on a B6/SJL F1 hybrid background. BACE1-/-\nmice on a C57/B6 background were obtained from Jackson\nLaboratories (strain #006554). Non-transgenic agematched\nB6/SJL or C57/B6 mice were used as controls.\"\n\n\"Human immunofluorescence confocal microscopy\nHuman AD sections were processed using the same method\nas mouse,\n\n13/4/2017 Pim\n- the strongest information is presented in Fig.3 which is on mouse tissue. This I use as the annotated species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_406" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

